content: 1. The app seems to use a tablet UI, so even at Larger Text Size everything is way too small! I can't hit anything properly or read when all my other apps (including regular Facebook app) are sized normal! 2. The reactions are not showing properly ever and flicker or are blank. 3. I cannot upload multiple pictures at once. When I select multiple pictures and hit next, nothing happens during making a post. 4. When typing a comment sometimes the box you type in is too small. S21+ One UI 4.1

A lot of issues. When posting pictures to a group all of your text gets deleted. You have to edit the post and add the text all over again. When notified of a new post within a group, once you click on the notification it takes you to a completely different post or different group. This had been happened since the last update. On Android 11.

Promises with little delivery. Videos still auto-play. Android notifications don't take you to the post; sometimes they take you to the top of your feed in the app, sometimes they don't do anything. Half the time the same notification re-appears after leaving the app or doesn't disappear at all. There is no Parent Dashboard for those using Messenger Kids. There is a display telling you that, but it stays open for only half a second. When you save a post, it always says displays a quick "Unsaved" and then disappears. In all, this app has very little quality control. More like an afterthought.

Buggiest app I've ever used. That's just marketplace which is the only reason i use this POS. After a couple weeks the browsing of categories stopped working. No results. Search can't use exclusion terms. Defaults to incld shipping every time you navigate. Unsaving works half the time. Error accessing the account page, sometimes. Tried deleting the app and the folder on my phone and reinstalling. Just figured that ads are shown that are actually deleted. No one was replying so it must not send

I've always tried to avoid Facebook but recently decided to try it out. I'm finding this app's notifications to be buggy and extremely obnoxious. I have to deal with each notification twice. There's the initial notification and the repeat after I open the app. Until I open the app, the notifications are stockpiled to blast all at once when I finally do open it. Being notified a second time is pointless. Being notified 30 times in 2 seconds is absurd. This indie company needs to ramp up QA.

Used to be glitchy but good enough. Now suddenly extremely slow. Seriously Facebook?? I'm about to uninstall. I don't even like to use FB on my computer because it's extremely slow on there too but I can't deal with this. I had to switch to this because the standard FB app was such a resource hog, constantly requiring more and more memory until I simply couldn't update it. This app WAS an acceptable alternative. It was glitchy and has issues but it got the job done... not anymore. I guess this is good motivation to stop letting FB consume so much of my time and attention.

The load times are annoying. It kept taking my 15 second gif and uploading it as a photo. The controls are very minimal and it doesn't allow you to edit as much as the regular app. If you truly want to downsize and save data be my guest but the normal app is far superior in my opinion and worth the data. Facebook doesn't use enough data in my opinion to justify having a lite version.

Works, sure. I still don't understand why I can edit posts until I'm blue in the face...but attach a picture and can't do anything. Post one picture, sure...try to make a second post with another picture, "Processing..." and remains at ZERO percent until I kill the app and fire it up again. Don't even get me started on trying to use Marketplace. The things I do to save space on my phone though...but these seem like easy fixes.

Absolutely garbage now, I cant view any pictures or videos, they show up in a tiny lil box so small you can't see it, and the videos have the mute button over them so its impossible to see it even if you could, and on top of that everytime you tap a photo to see it the app crashes. I don't what they did in the update but it made this app completely garbage and absolutely useless and a waste of space.

I'm giving it 1 star today not because it is bad overall, but because I hope this would draw the attention of developers. Lite has had a problem with images for more than an year and it hasn't been fixed yet. When you scroll down the feed, a large image is displayed cropped. In the regular Facebook app, when you click on that cropped image, it expands to its full size. In Lite, when you click the cropped image, it opens the post, but the image remains cropped, so you can't see its full content.

If you don't want the full Facebook app taking up space on your phone, just use Facebook through your phone's browser. This app looks and interacts similar to their mobile web page, but is so much less efficient. Posting and settings are limited and videos glitch out and freeze on a daily basis. It's also slower than my web browser. Great idea to have a smaller app, but the whole point of an app like this is to have a program that runs better and is more customizable than the web page.

Addictive features and deceptive ads. Ads aren't clearly marked and are disguised as posts by my friends. Whenever I try to share a video, instead of automatically closing the app, it stays open and plugs me right onto my feed. I don't even know if my post went through, so I go looking for it, and then I'm scrolling for hours.

Update 11.30.19- All you can do now is go on main feed. You can't click on friends page nor notifications. It doesn't download or allow you to see anything. I installed this app. It worked fine the first day. The second day, most images/photos weren't appearing. I just saw blank white spaces where they should be even after refreshing. I was able to see the images when I opened a browser app and used the Facebook mobile web page. So, I uninstalled FB lite. I will use the mobile website. That has worked well for me. There is no advantage to installing another app - especially when it fails.

Lite does not appear to have the option to place a friend on the Restricted list. This is a crucial element of Facebook & should not be ignored. Also, the event page options are ridiculously restricted. There should at least be an option to copy the text of the address even if it doesn't automatically open GPS. There are many benefits to this app & I'm trying to see the difficulties as reminders to reduce screen time, but it may not work out if there are so many functions that are just not possible.

I like the simpler, lighter UI and the fact that it's still reasonably full-featured. I also like the fact that it has dark mode before even the full version. But there is a major bug that makes keyboard presses not register when typing. I've experienced this twice and had the app for less than 24 hours on an S20 FE. No other apps are exhibiting this behavior and a force-close of the app didn't fix it. Guess it's back to the main app or a third-party solution.

Also, I'd like for the developers to create a dark mode for the web/mobile/mobile lite versions of Facebook and Messenger! I have a Google Pixel 2.

If Facebook is going to insist on bundling their app with my phone, this is the version they should include. It doesn't look quite as pretty, but it also doesn't kill your battery or data plan like the "full version" does. I'm glad Facebook is making an effort to cater to older devices, but I recommend this version of the app to all of my clients, no matter what device they have. It's far more resource-efficient than the full version, and still includes all the features they need.

Hopefully, in the near future I will say what this app does well. For now I'm only going to mention the things that it could do better: 1. Include in the App's settings, its notification sound. 2. Enable prioritization of notifications and how frequently to receive them. 3. Fine tune notifications, so it automatically goes to the post mentioned in the notice.

This app doesn't use so much data and storage space as the full app, and it runs more smoothly. Sometimes, you miss out on weird new stuff, like certain games, but that's not too important to me. The only problem I have is that when a post in another language is too long, sometimes it won't let me click "See More" after choosing "See Translation," so I might not get to read the full text. Overall, it's a better experience.

This is a good alternative app to the regular FB app. It is light ad does not use up a lot of phone space. The reason I did not give it 5 stars is because of the ads. Especially the regular FB app ad that keeps popping up. Does not make sense because it's the reason I chose this light app. It eat up too much space!

A lot like the regular FB app. The only real issues for me with the "Lite" version are the 'sometimes' difficult problems uploading large image files & the responsiveness of the app as a whole when opening links compared to the full version. All in all not bad & a good use to have one account always signed into FB Lite & the other in FB regular without having to log out/log in.

I do like how the app does not take up as much space on my phone as the regular version. One of my minor quibbles is not being able to see all the comments on news pages or be given the option to do so. I'm not as interested in how the algorithm wants me to engage with the material. Also, I shouldn't have to upload any contacts into the app for a friend's list that already exists.

This does not slow down my phone near as much as the full-blown Facebook app. One flaw is when I'm watching a Facebook video in full screen landscape mode, if I lay the phone down flat then it flips back every time into the smaller portrait mode orientation. The only way around this that I have found this to prop the phone up and not lay it down flat. If you could fix this then I would gladly rate you five stars. Using LG-V20.

Everything fine for a lite version. However, there are little details to correct. One of the biggest, is that when tapping on a photo to see it in full size, text is still appearing at the bottom and cannot be hidden by tapping the photo in fulk size. It would be very helpful to correct things like this.

I really liked this app...up till today. It's much better than the original Facebook. But now it's got a sort of disageable bug: when I try to give my opinion on something ( with an icon 😀😰😡 etc.. ) the icons sort of vibrate and you have to guess which one it is. Please fix it!

This app is so adorable, but the comment section is like a chrome other people saying that is. It can be also research in our modules in "discover" thats why i like it. If you turn off the data the videos youve watched is already open/or playing .

Only had the light version for a day or so and so far it seems to have fixed most of the annoyances I had with the full version so at the moment it seems to be a keeper we'll see how things pan out long-term....

This app is (arguably) what the 'normal' Facebook app should be. Sames goes with Messenger Lite. I was disappointed to find out, however, that the app does not support security keys properly. After enrolling a couple YubiKeys recently, I was unable to sign in to my account on this app. The app displayed a screen telling me I'd get a code by SMS. This was thankfully not true since I had intentionally disabled SMS as a backup.
